\begin_inset Formula $f(x)$
\end_inset

 is locally integrable for all intervals 
\begin_inset Formula $[a,b]$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Consider the 18.01 derivative of 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x)$
\end_inset

, which gives 
\begin_inset Formula $f'(x)=\begin{cases}
\frac{1}{x} & x\neq0\\
\mbox{undefined} & x=0
\end{cases}$
\end_inset

